The internal indicator lamp is lit and shows no observable internal faults. Since this lamp is connected in parallel with the main load and is functioning correctly when power is supplied and the switch is operated, this strongly suggests the issue lies with the main load itself rather than with the power supply or control circuit.

Based on your inspection, possible causes in the main load include:

- BurnedFilaments: The main load (likely another lamp or resistive element) may have internal filament damage preventing it from operating.
- LampImproperlyInstalled: The main load could be incorrectly installed or not making proper contact.

